The paper deals with image deblurring, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The proposed method explicitly handles various realistic image degradations such as pixel saturation, noise, quantization, and non-linear camera response function. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the method involves stochastic optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using a dataset, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
